l-track, socialist-capitalist economic system. Taken together, these changes demonstrate how economic development and culture interact in a postsocialist society, in contrast to the way they work in the mature capitalist economies of the West. That economic reforms have affected many aspects of Chinese society is well known, but this is the first comprehensive analysis of market influences in the literary field. This book thus offers a fresh perspective on the inner workings of contemporary Chinese society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aBooksellers and booksellingxChina. 0aBooksellers and booksellingzChina. 0aLibrairiexChinexChinaxChinaxChinesisch. 0aPublishers and publishingxChina. 0aPublishers and publishingzChina. 0aÉditionxChine. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476737840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804767378423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804767378/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles